post_text: The Glenview Park District will live stream their virtual grand reopening of the Glenview Community Ice Center tomorrow!
shared_text:
Glenview Park District
September 10 at 5:27 PM ·

Join the Glenview Community Ice Center live on Facebook for a virtual grand reopening this Saturday. A live stream countdown begins at 9:30 a.m. with a slideshow of project photos. The celebration kicks off at 10 a.m. with the one and only Wayne Messmer singing the national anthem. Check back on Facebook to learn what else we have planned for this exciting event. Learn more http://bit.ly/GCICGrandReopening
#GCIC #Love2Skate #NiceIce #skating #figureskater #iceskater #iceskate #hockey #icehockey #figureskatinglife #adultsskatetoo #GlenviewStars #GlenviewBlades

post_text:
Calling CAMP LOL & LIL' families (and any families of EC-2 students who want to follow CAMP activities on their own)! Have you participated in Family Talk Friday (FTF)? This week's CAMP theme is "Grow," and as you move through the week, you can plan for Friday! FTF offers age-appropriate conversation starters and learning opportunities to grow your understanding of racism. Visit the CAMP LOL & LIL' site, and then click on the Families tab in the upper right corner. https://sites.google.com/glenview34.org/d34camplol/home?authuser=0

If you had a good FTF experience last week discussing empathy ("Wander in someone else's shoes"), please share!

post_text: Today, Illinois Governor J.B. Pritzker announced that he will extend the stay-at-home order through the end of May. His order also makes face coverings mandatory statewide, and allows schools to establish procedures for pick up of necessary supplies. We will share information on those procedures in District 34 when they are finalized. See the fill order here: https://www2.illinois.gov/Pages/news-item.aspx?ReleaseID=21459
shared_text:

text:
Today, Illinois Governor J.B. Pritzker announced that he will extend the stay-at-home order through the end of May. His order also makes face coverings mandatory statewide, and allows schools to establish procedures for pick up of necessary supplies. We will share information on those procedures in District 34 when they are finalized. See the fill order here: https://www2.illinois.gov/Pages/news-item.aspx?ReleaseID=21459

WWW2.ILLINOIS.GOV
Illinois News - Illinois.gov

April 10 at 1:37 PM ·

Winner, winner, $50 towards a Glenview purchased item or dinner! Introducing a new contest: Snapshots while Social Distancing! 📸 Photo theme: Glenview wildlife! All the details are 👇! But in a nutshell: Get outside (6 feet apart & wear a mask), take a snapshot of Glenview wildlife 🦆🐝🐦, tag the Village on Facebook, Twitter or IG (@glenviewvillage) and use #HealthySixFeet and #BikeGlenview Submissions are due by 5 pm April 17! On April 20, you, the "viewers" will vote for your favorite photo! Most votes is the winner!
